##### Matthew 28
- **Matthew 28:1 (KJV):**  
	_**"In the end of the sabbath, as it began to dawn toward the first day of the week, came Mary Magdalene and the other Mary to see the sepulchre."**_
	- sabbath = sundown on Friday to sundown on Saturday (Sabado)
	- sepulchre = the burial place of Jesus Christ, described in the Gospels.
	- Mary Magdalene - "Magdalene" indicates she was from **Magdala**, a town on the western shore of the Sea of Galilee.
		- She is mentioned at least **12 times** in the Gospels, more than most of Jesus' disciples.
		- Mary was one of Jesus’ closest followers and a key member of the group of women who supported His ministry financially (Luke 8:1-3).
		- She is described as having been healed by Jesus of "seven demons" (Mark 16:9, Luke 8:2), which some interpret as a sign of significant spiritual or psychological healing.
		- Mary Magdalene was present at the crucifixion of Jesus (Matthew 27:55–56, John 19:25).
		- Unlike most of the male disciples who fled, she stayed near the cross with other women, including Mary, the mother of Jesus.
		- Mary is the **first person to witness the resurrected Christ** (John 20:11–18, Mark 16:9).
		- Mary Magdalene is venerated as a saint in many Christian traditions.